Liam's User stories


1. Smart Journey Planning (Features 1, 3, 4)


User story:

"As a UCD student living in Portobello, I want to see real-time weather and 30-minute occupancy predictions so that I can decide whether to cycle or take the bus to my 9 AM lecture."



Acceptance criteria:

Check Live Weather

Given the user is on the Home screen,

When the system detects the location as Dublin,

Then the system displays real-time temperature, rain probability, and cycling alerts.


Predict Future Availability

Given the user is on the interactive map,

When the user selects a specific station and clicks "30-min Prediction",

Then the system displays the predicted number of bikes and stands based on ML patterns.




2. Active Rental Tracking (Feature 10)


User story:

"As a budget-conscious student, I want to track my current rental duration in real-time so that I can return the bike within the 30-minute free period to avoid extra charges."



Acceptance criteria:

Start Live Timer

Given a bike has been successfully unlocked,

When the rental session begins,

Then the system displays a dynamic timer on the main interface tracking minutes used.


Estimate Surcharge

Given the user is currently on an active ride,

When the rental duration exceeds 30 minutes,

Then the system automatically calculates and displays the current estimated rental cost.




3. Account & Subscription Management (Features 5, 6)


User story:

"As a heavy user, I want to manage my Annual Subscription and top-up my account credit via my login so that my daily commute is never interrupted by payment issues."



Acceptance criteria:

Manage Subscription Plans

Given the user has logged into their account,

When the user navigates to the "Subscriptions" section,

Then the system displays options to choose or renew Daily, Monthly, or Annual plans.


Top-up Account Credit

Given the user is in the payment settings,

When the user inputs an amount and confirms payment,

Then the system updates the account balance and displays a success message.




4. Interactive Navigation & Support (Features 2, 7)



User story:

"As a commuter traveling to different work locations, I want to see precise station info and access 'How-to' guides so that I can find docks that support credit card payments and return bikes correctly."



Acceptance criteria:

Filter Station Services

Given the user is viewing the interactive map,

When the user taps on a specific station marker,

Then the system displays a popup with the station name, distance, and available services (e.g., Credit Card terminal).


Access Instructional Guide

Given the user needs help with the rental process,

When the user selects the "How to" option from the menu,

Then the system displays step-by-step visual instructions for renting and returning bikes.




5. Local Engagement (Features 8, 9)


User story:

"As a Dublin resident, I want to access local news and special student offers so that I can stay informed about city events and save money on cycling-related costs."



Acceptance criteria:

View Dublin Updates

Given the user is on the main app dashboard,

When the user navigates to "Dublin News",

Then the system displays a feed of local news and traffic alerts.


Claim Special Offers

Given the user is in the "Special Offer" section,

When the user selects a student-specific discount,

Then the system provides the redemption details and applies the offer to the user's profile.









Sarah's User stories


1. Predicting Office Dock Availability (Feature 4)


User story:
"As a worker with a strict clock-in time, I want to see a 15-minute prediction of empty stands near my office so that I can decide whether to proceed or head to a backup station without being late for my meeting."



Acceptance criteria:

Short-term Precision Prediction

Given the user is on the station information page for their destination in Ballsbridge,

When the user views the "15-min Prediction" section,

Then the system displays the forecasted number of empty stands specifically for that timeframe.


Visual Availability Warning

Given the ML model predicts the station will be full within 15 minutes,

When the user views the station marker on the map,

Then the marker changes color (e.g., to Red) to provide an immediate visual warning.




2. Weather-based Attire Protection (Feature 1)


User story:
"As a professional analyst wearing formal work attire, I want to receive precise rain intensity alerts so that I can switch to a taxi during heavy rain to avoid ruining my clothes."



Acceptance criteria:

Rain Intensity Monitoring

Given the user is on the Home screen checking the Dublin Weather,

When the forecast indicates "Heavy Rain" during the user's commute window,

Then the system displays a prominent alert recommending an alternative transport mode.


Temperature & Road Condition Warning

Given the temperature is near freezing (below 2Â°C),

When the user checks the weather update before leaving,

Then the system provides a "Slippery Road" warning to indicate dangerous cycling conditions.




3. Smart & Efficient Login (Feature 5)


User story:
"As a professional in a rush to get to meetings, I want a smart and efficient login process so that I can access station data instantly without re-entering credentials while on the go."



Acceptance criteria:

Biometric Integration

Given the user has an existing account and is on the Login page,

When the user chooses to enable "Smart Login,"

Then the system allows future access via Face ID or fingerprint authentication.


One-Tap Access to Favorites

Given the user has successfully logged in,

When the app opens during peak commute hours (e.g., 8:00 AM),

Then the map automatically centers on the user's "Favorite" stations near their home and office.



4. Weekly Pattern Management (Feature 4)


User story:
"As a commuter who finds Mondays particularly high-demand, I want to see hourly occupancy bar charts so that I can decide to leave 10 minutes earlier to guarantee a bike."



Acceptance criteria:

Hourly Occupancy Bar Chart

Given the user is viewing the details of a specific station,

When the user expands the "Historical Trends" section,

Then the system displays a bar chart showing the average occupancy for each hour of the day.


Day-of-Week Comparison

Given the user is viewing the trend chart,

When the user selects "Monday" from the day filter,

Then the system updates the chart to show historical data specific to Mondays to help the user plan for high-demand days.



5. Rental History & Cost Verification (Feature 10)


User story:
"As a budget-conscious professional, I want to track my rental history and durations so that I can verify my subscription usage and ensure I am staying within my free 30-minute window."



Acceptance criteria:

Ride Duration Confirmation

Given the user has completed a trip and returned the bike,

When the user navigates to the "Rental History" page,

Then the system displays the start time, end time, and total duration of the trip.


Cost Accuracy Check

Given the user is reviewing a past rental entry,

When the duration exceeded the 30-minute free period,

Then the system displays the breakdown of the surcharge applied to their account balance.
